name: Creation of Giratina
description: Everyone loves Pokemon, right? Right! In the beginning, there was nothing. Then our lord Arceus spoke, "Let there be Pokemon." And it was good. Part of a series of religious parodies, this piece features Arceus creating one of his children, Giratina. These bad boys are printed on heavy weight, high-gloss premium photo paper. These are available in two sizes; 8.5"x11" or 13"x19". Prints will be sent via First Class Mail with 2-5 day delivery within the United States, or 2-3 weeks internationally. If you would like a more expedited shipping, please email me. I'll be more than happy to accommodate you :)

name: Krooked Krookodile
description: Everyone loves Pokemon, right? Right! Gen 5 gave us some fantastically sassy new dark types. Whenever I play through Black or White, I have the worst time trying to decide between sandile and scraggy. This last time, I went with sandile, and he became one meeeaaaan old krookodile! These bad boys are printed on heavy weight, high-gloss premium photo paper. These are available in two sizes; 8.5"x11" or 13"x19". name: Swarm
description: Everyone loves Pokemon, right? Right! Pinsir is one of those un-sung poke's from gen 1. He's not great at battling, but he IS great at looking badass! This piece was inspired by the pokedex entry describing how pinsir bury themselves underground during the night, then rise the next day. Couple that with a swarm, and you've got some scary Dawn of the Living Bugs goin on! These bad boys are printed on heavy weight, high-gloss premium photo paper. These are available as a 10"x10" print. Prints will be sent via First Class Mail with 2-5 day delivery within the United States, or 2-3 weeks internationally. If you would like a more expedited shipping, please email me. I'll be more than happy to accommodate you :)
